FILE: middleware.rs
MOD: api/middleware
ROLE: Tower middleware — per-project token-bucket rate limiting keyed by X-Project header
EP: ProjectRateLimiter::new; ProjectRateLimiter::check; rate_limit_middleware
STAB: stable
INV:
  - ProjectRateLimiter is a single shared instance (Arc in AppState) — NOT one instance per request
  - Buckets are per-project: DefaultKeyedRateLimiter<String> maintains independent quota per project name
  - rate_limit_middleware reads X-Project header ONLY — it does NOT call broker, DB, or auth logic
  - Requests with missing or empty X-Project pass through unthrottled — downstream auth rejects them
  - Returns 429 with Retry-After: 1 on limit exceeded — no body delivery attempt
  - Quota is configured at startup via BROKER_RATE_LIMIT env var — not per-project from DB (v1)
  - Applied only to state-mutating routes: /send, /channels/*/subscribe, /channels/*/unsubscribe, /messages, /messages/peek
  - NOT applied to: /projects/register, /agents/register, /agents, /presence, /health, /ws upgrade, /admin/*
  - WS per-stanza rate limiting is out of scope — would require in-broker logic
LOOK: route group in routes.rs that applies the layer; AppState.rate_limiter field
CHK: cargo test middleware; verify per-project bucket isolation test; verify pass-through for missing X-Project
CNTR: api/middleware::rate_limit_middleware must_not broker/state
CNTR: api/middleware::rate_limit_middleware must_not db/repository
DEPS-ON: api/routes
